'''Decor Cabinets Ltd''' (also known as the Decor Cabinet Company) is a [[Manitoba]] based manufacturer of custom [[kitchen]], bath and specialty [[cabinetry]].

In 2018, The FDMC 300 group ranked Decor as the 120th largest furniture manufacturer in North America.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.woodworkingnetwork.com/fdmc-300/2018/decor-cabinets-ltd |title=Decor Cabinets Ltd. |work= Woodworking Network |location=U.S. }}</ref> This publication covers trends and news that affect small cabinet shops to large woodworking plants in North America.

Decor Cabinets currently employs more than 500 people between its head office, production plant and [[showroom]].<ref name="research">{{cite news |url=http://www.nrc-cnrc.gc.ca/eng/irap/success/2014/decor_cabinets.html |title=Improving productivity and cabinetry with new engineering capabilities |work= National Research Council Canada |location=Canada }}</ref>

==History==

[[File:Decor Cabinets Headquarters .jpg|thumb|right|350px|Decor Cabinets Ltd headquarters in Morden Manitoba, Canada]]

Decor Cabinets Ltd. began producing framed cabinets in [[Portage la Prairie]], Manitoba in 1977.

The company produced framed and frameless products for several years and then moved exclusively into frameless production. In 1985 the company shifted its focus to custom frameless products with full access cabinetry. In 1990 Decor moved to its current location in [[Morden]], Manitoba.<ref name="industry">{{cite news |url=http://industrytoday.com/article_view.asp?ArticleID=2261 |title=Cabinets with a Purpose |work= Industry Today |location=Canada }}</ref>

In 2007, Decor Cabinets became the first company in Manitoba to be certified through the WOODMARK Quality Certification Program.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.woodworkingnetwork.com/wood-market-trends/woodworking-industry-news/production-woodworking-news/decor_cabinets_earns_first_woodmark_certification_in_manitoba_127710718.html#sthash.ffY1aea5.dpbs |title=Decor Cabinets Earns First WOODMARK Certification in Manitoba |work= Woodworking Network |location=U.S. }}</ref>

The [[company]] was able to gain [[market share]] despite fierce competition and the [[United States housing bubble|housing market crash in the U.S.]] that started in 2008.<ref name="research"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/work-share-agreements-saving-jobs-in-manitoba-1.814724 |title=Work-share agreements saving jobs in Manitoba |work= CBC News |location=Canada }}</ref>

==The company==

Decor Cabinets is owned by Stan and Connie Pauls. Its dealer network includes four Canadian provinces and 33 U.S. states.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.woodworkingcanada.com/r5/showkiosk.asp?listing_id=5633640 |title=Stan and Connie Pauls purchase Decor Cabinets Ltd. |work= Woodworking Network |location=U.S. }}</ref>

==Community involvement==

The company supports a variety of local and international organizations.<ref name="research" />

In November 2010, Decor Cabinets sponsored the construction of a [[Splash pad|Spray Park]] in Morden.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.pembinatoday.ca/2010/11/10/decor-sponsoring-spray-park |title=Decor sponsoring spray park |work= The Morden Times |location=Canada }}</ref>

===Decor charity classic golf tournament===

Since 2004, Decor has hosted the annual ''Decor Charity Classic Golf Tournament''. All proceeds are divided equally among four worthwhile charities with Decor Cabinets matching half of the all net proceeds. Since its inception the [[tournament]] has brought in over $1,040,000<ref>{{cite news |url=https://pembinavalleyonline.com/local/decor-charity-classic-raises-72-000-for-local-charities |title=Decor Classic Hits Million Dollar Milestone with Annual Tournament |work= Pembina Valley Online |location=Canada }}</ref>

===CorImpact===

Decor Cabinets runs a program called ''CorImpact'' in partnership with [[Opportunity International]] Canada to support education in African countries<ref>{{cite news |url=http://opportunityinternational.ca/decor-cabinet-company-c254.php |title=CorImpact by Decor Cabinet Company |work= Opportunity International |location=Canada }}</ref>, micro-financing for entrepreneurs in Latin American countries amongst other activities.

==Environmental commitment==

In 2010 Decor was awarded the first CLER Program Green Award by M.S.T.W. Planning District in Morden through its program ''Greencore''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.pembinavalleyonline.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=16395&Itemid=59 |title=First Green Award Handed Out |work= Pembina Valley Online |location=Canada }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.pembinatoday.ca/2010/04/28/business-decor-honoured-for-going-green |title=Decor honored for going green |work= The Morden Times |location=Canada }}</ref>

Decor is part of the [[Environmental Stewardship]] Program (ESP).<ref>{{cite news |url=http://greencabinetsource.org/ESP_Certified_Manufacturers |title=ESP Certified Manufacturers & Brands |work= Canadian Kitchen Cabinet Association |location=Canada }}</ref> The ESP voluntary program gives cabinet manufacturers a way to demonstrate their commitment to [[sustainability]] and helps identify products that are better for the environment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://greencabinetsource.org/Learn_about_ESP |title=Learn about ESP |work= The Kitchen Cabinet Manufacturers Association (KCMA) |location=Canada }}</ref>

==Health & Safety==

In July 2018 Decor Cabinets achieved its SAFE Work Certification by Made Safe.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://madesafe.ca/2019/02/05/decor-cabinets-achieves-safe-work-certification-made-safe/ |title=Decor Cabinets achieves SAFE Work Certification by Made Safe |work= CME Manitoba |location=Canada }}</ref>

